media.altText:
A comic of two foxes, one of whom is blue, the other is green. In this one, Blue and Gren are sitting at a table, looking at a game with cards and little red tokens.
Green: I don't do well with rules if I don't get what they're for. If I know why the rule exists, and it makes sense, I'll remember the logic behind it.

Green lays his ears down and stares at the board angrily.
Green: But random, arbitrary rules? No. Poison. Does not compute.

Blue sighs, looking exhausted. Green's frustration is gone, and he looks at the table again eagerly.
Blue: We don't have to learn this board game if you hate it.
Green: No, I'll figure it out.
